trend_summary: Across the sequence, suburban fabric thickens: housing and mixed-use blocks fill gaps, industrial estates grow, and new roads knit the zones together. Forest and open land shrink, especially near the airport and western factories, though a small northern clearing re-greens later. Overall pattern remains suburban with medium, steadily rising built-up density.
notable_changes: Residential infill removes many vacant plots in the central sector.
Industrial parks extend westward and eastward along main highways.
A new arterial road links the southern industrial zone to eastern suburbs.
Airport apron and logistics buildings enlarge toward the southeast.
Forest margins contract, while a northern quarry area shows later revegetation.
